16	//             missing_condition_ids: string[] }
17	//     → 500 { error: 'SERVER_MISCONFIGURED' | 'DB_ERROR' }
18	//
19	// Auth: Marketify JWT (HS256, MARKETIFY_JWT_SECRET). Deployed with
20	//       verify_jwt=false at the gateway because the gateway only knows
21	//       about Supabase's own JWT secret — the handler enforces auth.
22	//
23	// Request shape — the US-045 story AC specifies `{ application_id,
24	// video_url, post_condition_affirmations }`. The tech-architecture spec
25	// §5.7 names a future-compatible `{ videos: [...] }` array shape; per
26	// the Ralph convention when story AC and spec disagree at the field
27	// level the story AC wins. The DB layer models multi-video via
28	// `submission_videos.sort_order` so expanding to an array later is a
29	// non-breaking change to this endpoint.
30	//
31	// URL validation (docs/tech-architecture.md §3h):
32	//   - TikTok canonical + shortlinks accepted; canonical gives us the
33	//     numeric `external_id`.
34	//   - TikTok oEmbed endpoint is called to prove the URL points at a
35	//     real, currently-resolvable post. A 404 from TikTok → 422
36	//     INVALID_VIDEO_URL. Network/5xx failures from TikTok → 500.
37	//   - Instagram URLs are validated by regex-shape only because IG
38	//     oEmbed requires an app-level Meta token that we do not currently
39	//     have provisioned. See `_shared/oembed.ts` header.
40	//
41	// Affirmation gate — the spec treats POST conditions (e.g.
42	// "must_mention", "family_friendly") as creator attestations at
43	// submit-time rather than machine-checkable facts. Every `post`-kind
44	// condition on the application's pinned listing_version_id must appear
45	// in `post_condition_affirmations` with a literal `true` value. Missing
46	// or `false` entries → 422 INCOMPLETE_AFFIRMATIONS with the offending
47	// ids so the client can re-surface them.
48	//
49	// Concurrency — the RPC acquires a row lock on the application
50	// (FOR UPDATE) so a duplicate submit interleaving with this one is
51	// serialised and the second request receives SUBMISSION_EXISTS. The
52	// partial unique index `submissions_open_uniq` is the DB backstop.
